Task 3: Refactoring Open-Source Collaborative Editor
Objective

Take an open-source collaborative editor project and refactor it for readability and performance.

Implementation

Readability changes:

Clear variable/function naming.

Added comments for better understanding.

Consistent coding style.

Performance improvements:

Implemented debounce for frequent updates.

Optimized room-based event broadcasting.

Introduced caching for file persistence.

Maintainability improvements:

Split code into sockets.js, utils/, server.js.

Reusable helper functions (logger, debounce).

Impact

Readability: Modularized code, easier debugging.

Performance: Lower CPU/network usage, scalable design.

Maintainability: Easier to add new features (auth, DB, CRDT).
